The paper deals with algorithms for finding outlier correlations in binary data, which is a problem in computational complexity and data mining. The use of correlation amplifiers and zigzag-product expanders suggests connections to topics in computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on explicit constructions and derandomization also suggests connections to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
